  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user i want to have better experience with chats. \r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: When i am in the middle of any chat (1x1, group or public) like i am reading history for example and new message arrives to this particular chat - there is an autoscroll function that scrolls the chat for 1 message down (if 1 new was received). I find this confusing to me comparing to other messengers.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\n1. chat is scrolled down right after new message arrived. This could be annoying as i want to continue reading history for example, app should not force me to read new messages\r\n\r\n2. chat is not scrolled at all when new message arrives, but a notification shown (like a banner) saying `you have 2 unread messages` with dynamic counter (or without counter). the banner is clickable and directs me right at the bottom of the chat when i tap it. The banner does not prevent me from reading history or scrolling chat (like Viber or Skype does).\r\n\r\n@denis-sharypin @chadyj please advise\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status on 2 devices\r\n- Create 1x1 chat with those 2 devices\r\n- Text ~30 messages in chat so user has history\r\n- On 1 device scroll the history to somehwere in the middle\r\n- On 2 device text new message to this chat\r\n- Pay attention to the device 1\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: develop\r\n* Operating System: Android, iOS",
